caption: Quiet and cozy place to drink some coffee and snack on something yummy.

Giving this place a one star review because of their professionalism. Employee’s operate with their face masks either completely off or under their nose. My friend and I only realized this AFTER we started consuming our orders. Kept seeing one woman always taking it off behind counter and putting it back on when walking to a table. A male entered the premises after I ate half my panini and with NO MASK ON, went behind the counter, touched everything, operated the coffee machine and even laughed in my face after I commented to a waitress about it. Apparently “We cant tell him what to do” was her response. Oh okay, sure; that’s nice. Let me make it very clear this establishment lost my business. I take this virus very seriously for myself, my mother, my family, and to see an establishment, which serves food, not practicing social distant safe practices is super off putting. I think what is more disappointing is the interior is really nice and warm and the food was good but that means nothing when my health is in jeopardy. I lost my appetite upon learning the Corona virus may be lurking behind the counter and encourage avoiding at all cost

I did not encounter any of the rudeness that many of the reviews have mentioned. When my family and I went, we ordered a Frutta di Bosco, a Monte Crisco panini, 2 Italiano paninis, and 1 Francisco panini.  The Frutta di Bosco was scrumptious and definitely the highlight of the meal. So good in fact that we ordered another one...which never arrived.  My panini was so so. I spotted a bit of the pesto color, but I couldn’t taste it. Instead, the whole thing tasted sour, as if there was too much vinegar. Regardless, at least it was very filling. My mom couldn’t even finish the 2nd half.  Overall, service was very slow. They only have 2 waitresses I think. When we asked for a box for doggie bag and for a check, we waited around for like 5-10 minutes. And as I mentioned earlier, the second fruit tart never came.
